This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on neural architecture search for super-resolution tasks. Additionally, it incorporates both evolution algorithms and reinforced learning methods, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The use of genetic algorithms also suggests a potential fit for the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the incorporation of reinforced control suggests a potential fit for the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
